<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:19PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Pittsylvania County through 945 PM EDT...
At 919 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hurt, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail. Cloud-to-
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mt Airy Virginia...
and Straightstone.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
